  "title": "rapid-hemifield-object-eeg",
  "description": "This EEG dataset examines the neural dynamics of visual object coding across cerebral hemispheres using rapid serial visual presentation. Participants viewed object and word stimuli presented at 5 Hz to the left visual field, right visual field, or central location while performing an orthogonal red target detection task. The dataset provides insights into how visual information is processed within and across hemispheric boundaries during peripheral vision.",
  "methods_description": "Visual stimuli (objects and words) were presented at 5 Hz to the left visual field, right visual field, or centrally while participants performed a red target detection task. EEG data were recorded during these visual presentation trials.",
